        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 2:13PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Olympic Valley, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alpine Meadows, Prosser Creek Reservoir, Tahoe City, Olympic Valley,
Boca Reservoir, Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Northstar, Hirschdale,
Truckee, Northstar Ski Area, Granite Flat Campground, Lakeside
Campground, Glenshire-Devonshire, Ca 89 At Placer-Nevada Co Line,
Olympic Valley Ski Area, Dollar Point, Alpine Meadows Campground,
Tahoe State Rec Area Campground, Boca Campground, and Truckee-Tahoe
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
